# API Adapter Rules

## Hook Registration

- `hooks.json` must be at `cartridge/scripts/hooks.json`
- `package.json` must contain `"hooks": "./cartridge/scripts/hooks.json"`
- Hook names follow `dw.apps.{domain}.{subdomain}.{action}` pattern
- Each hook maps to a script file in `cartridge/scripts/hooks/`

## Hook Implementation

- Use `'use strict';` at the top of every file
- Export the hook function matching the action name: `exports.calculate`, `exports.commit`, `exports.cancel`
- Always return `dw.system.Status` (`new Status(Status.OK)` or `new Status(Status.ERROR)`)
- Never return `undefined` from a hook
- Wrap all basket/order modifications in `Transaction.wrap(function() { ... })`
- Call `lineItemCtnr.updateTotals()` before reading basket data

## Error Handling

- Never block checkout on API failures — fall back gracefully (e.g., zero tax)
- Return `Status.OK` with fallback behavior on API errors, `Status.ERROR` only for true system failures
- Log errors with `Logger.getLogger(category, scope)`
- Catch all exceptions with try/catch at the top level

## Script API Usage

- Import modules with `require('dw/...')`: Status, Transaction, Logger, Site, HTTPClient, Money, StringUtils
- Use `~/cartridge/scripts/...` for cartridge-relative imports
- Use `require()` not `importPackage()` (legacy)
- No npm packages — only `dw/*` Script API modules and your own cartridge code

## Configuration

- Read config from Site Preferences: `Site.getCurrent().getCustomPreferenceValue('MyApp_Key')`
- Never hardcode API credentials, URLs, or secrets in script files
- Define all configurable values as Site Custom Preferences via IMPEX
- Store API credentials in IMPEX service definitions

## Data Handling

- Use `dw/value/Money` for all currency values: `new Money(amount, currencyCode)`
- Check for null before accessing `shipment.getShippingAddress()` — may not exist early in checkout
- Use iterators correctly: `collection.iterator()` then `while (iter.hasNext()) { var item = iter.next(); }`

## Cartridge Naming

- Integration cartridges: `int_` prefix (e.g., `int_avatax`)
- Business Manager cartridges: `bm_` prefix (e.g., `bm_avatax`)
- Maximum 50 characters for cartridge directory name

## IMPEX

- Provide both `impex/install/` and `impex/uninstall/` directories
- Define custom attributes on Basket, Order, or SitePreferences as needed
- Group site preferences under an attribute group for Business Manager display
- Include service credentials, profiles, and definitions in `services.xml`
